Eskom will implement stage 2 load-shedding tonight. The power utility stated that stage 2 load-shedding will take place from 22:00 this evening until 05:00 tomorrow morning. Eskom said it lost three generating units today and had to implement emergency reserves to meet power demand. As a result, the emergency reserve levels are critically low, and load-shedding was required. The risk of further load-shedding tomorrow also remains high if generating units are not returned tonight, said Eskom. Eskom requested that South Africans make a concerted effort to reduce the amount of electricity they are using to lower power demand levels. It provided examples of how people should reduce their usage, which included instructions to: #POWERALERT 2 Date: 7 November 2019 Eskom will implement stage 2 loadshedding this evening from 22:00 until 05:00@News24 @SABCNewsOnline @IOL@ewnupdates @TimesLIVE @SowetanLIVE @SAfmnews @ukhoz pic.twitter.com/JUYsGDK4lc â€” Eskom Hld SOC Ltd (@Eskom_SA) November 7, 2019 